verbose_text: Both the SN and sEV fraction from iRAS cells induced an upregulation of several markers of senescence in normal HFFF2 compared to iC, as shown by a decrease in bromodeoxyuridine (BrdU) incorporation, an increase in p16 INK4A protein expression levels, the percentage of positive cells for phosphorylated-gammaH2AX (p-gammaH2AX), and the accumulation of p53 by immunofluorescence (IF) (XREF_FIG B and 1C).
evidence: SN and sEV fraction from iRAS cells induced an upregulation of several markers of senescence
